<p>As a Principal, John serves as the primary point of client contact during our engagements.  
His responsibilities vary by project but typically include project management and both architectural 
and development leadership roles.  John has the ability to understand our client's business goals, create a list 
of project requirements, translate these requirements into the language of developers and lead the development effort.</p>
<p>John Clarke came to Nevo from Circles Associates, Inc. in 2012 to lead Nevo's initial engagement with The Boston Company Asset Management.</p>
<p>He has since provided project and technical leadership on several Nevo projects, working at all levels of the technology stack.  John employs a "player/coach" leadership style: 
working as one of the development team while providing mentorship to more junior members and lending a sensitive ear to clients' needs.</p>
<p>With a passion for computing and broad experience in many software development environments, John functions as a versatile and well-rounded member of any software development team.</p>
John holds a BA in Mathematics with a minor in Computer Science from Boston University.

